item.title: Old RSCD version
item.dc:creator: @Zlacki Zlacki
item.description:
@Zlacki wrote:

[quote=“Fabrice L, post:3, topic:539688”][quote author=Zlacki link=topic=658530.msg4410730#msg4410730 date=1393546779]
This is a fairly useless project to post, at this point. Doesn’t eXemplar still have v2 up on svn somewhere?
[/quote]

It’s not a project… I never even touched it, it’s been on my computer since September 2007

Also, why is it useless?

I’m not that kind of guy that takes a ready to host server and change name… Some people actually want to make this a learning experience instead of a moneymaker[/quote]
Pointless project to post, it is a project, not yours but still a project.
Useless because this is basically varekd with a little less content, and varekd is well spread around. I just don’t see why anyone needs a blank RSCDaemon; write a server from scratch, it’s better.
It is well known how deep the problem slie in RSCDaemon.
